      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_59e3650d07b02f37078c5e77c3948029">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b47d34e94638d2b4b4865e866d0d9168">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of 16mm films produced by Ethan Allen Films on Sports [?] around 1960 in cooperation with the Yale University Athletic Association. The films, made for distribution to amatuer and professional teams, demonstrate baseball technique using Yale baseball players. Ethan Allen, Yale baseball coach from 1946 to 1968, narrates the films. Also included are videotapes of games and other team events.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
